ABUJA – Dr. Yusuf Datti Baba-Ahmed, the vice-presidential candidate of Labour Party, has claimed that results obtained from the INEC Result Viewing Portal (IReV) show that Peter Obi, presidential candidate of Labour Party won the February 25 presidential election in 19 states across Nigeria plus the FCT. Baba-Ahmed, who stated this in a tweet on Monday, also claimed results for PDP’s Atiku Abubakar in eight states; APC’s Bola Tinubu in seven states, whileNNPP’s Rabiu Kwankwaso won in two states. He, however, did not list the states. It would be recalled that the Independent National Electoral Commission, INEC, had on Wednesday, last week, declared the candidate of the All Progressives Congress, APC, Senator Bola Tinubu, as the winner of the February 25 poll. Below is a tweet obtained from the verified Twitter page of Yusuf Datti Baba-Ahmed: “This is the Results obtained from IReV Portal: LP: 19 States + FCTPDP: 8 States.APC: 7 States.NNPP: 2 States. It is going to be a long ride, but stay with me….